{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0154CVuKLvyXenSG36JFatMC","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Framings\n2\t\n3\tNamed structural insights, applied by classification: \"does `applies-when` match, and does\n4\t`misfires-when` NOT?\" Cite by name when used.\n5\t\n6\t---\n7\t\n8\t### overload-behind-conflicts\n9\tWhen several interpersonal problems surface at once around one person, suspect that person's\n10\tremaining capacity before treating each conflict individually. Conflicts are often the\n11\tsymptom, not the cause.\n12\t- born: 2026-07, distilled from live sessions\n13\t- applies-when: two or more troubles involving the same person, with different counterparties, in a short window\n14\t- misfires-when: the counterparties share a structural cause (policy change, reorg) — reducing it to the person misdiagnoses\n15\t\n16\t### shared-cause-behind-parallel-friction\n17\tWhen several *different* people independently raise friction about the same process or area in\n18\ta short window, suspect one upstream change they all touched before reading each pushback as\n19\tits own interpersonal problem. The common object is the tell.\n20\t- born: 2026-07, distilled from a live session\n21\t- applies-when: multiple unrelated people push back in the same window, and their complaints point at the same process/system/policy\n22\t- misfires-when: the frictions are about genuinely unrelated things with no shared object — then treat each on its own terms\n23\t\n24\t### suspect-the-instrument\n25\tA failing test, monitor, or check cannot distinguish \"the subject broke\" from \"the check\n26\tbroke.\" Verify the instrument before indicting the subject.\n27\t- born: 2026-07, distilled from a live debugging session\n28\t- applies-when: the claim \"X is broken\" rests on a single verification channel's failure\n29\t- misfires-when: multiple independent channels show the same failure — instrument-doubt is then a waste of time\n30\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c3a076da-efbb-414a-839b-b45dd0b1458e","uuid":"76a6c860-0dc4-440f-97cd-4fef30624780","timestamp":"2026-07-04T19:16:00.585Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/private/var/folders/b0/wkz515fj2yn3ncbxr7b8fr2r0000gn/T/fakeble-bench.q0dS1D/framing-application/arm-b/project/framings.md","content":"# Framings\n\nNamed structural insights, applied by classification: \"does `applies-when` match, and does\n`misfires-when` NOT?\" Cite by name when used.\n\n---\n\n### overload-behind-conflicts\nWhen several interpersonal problems surface at once around one person, suspect that person's\nremaining capacity before treating each conflict individually. Conflicts are often the\nsymptom, not the cause.\n- born: 2026-07, distilled from live sessions\n- applies-when: two or more troubles involving the same person, with different counterparties, in a short window\n- misfires-when: the counterparties share a structural cause (policy change, reorg) — reducing it to the person misdiagnoses\n\n### shared-cause-behind-parallel-friction\nWhen several *different* people independently raise friction about the same process or area in\na short window, suspect one upstream change they all touched before reading each pushback as\nits own interpersonal problem. The common object is the tell.\n- born: 2026-07, distilled from a live session\n- applies-when: multiple unrelated people push back in the same window, and their complaints point at the same process/system/policy\n- misfires-when: the frictions are about genuinely unrelated things with no shared object — then treat each on its own terms\n\n### suspect-the-instrument\nA failing test, monitor, or check cannot distinguish \"the subject broke\" from \"the check\nbroke.\" Verify the instrument before indicting the subject.\n- born: 2026-07, distilled from a live debugging session\n- applies-when: the claim \"X is broken\" rests on a single verification channel's failure\n- misfires-when: multiple independent channels show the same failure — instrument-doubt is then a waste of time\n","numLines":30,"startLine":1,"totalLines":30}}}
